    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Despite multiple credibility factor gaps identified across all 13 ASME V&V 40 factors, the assessment team has accepted this package under the Minimal profile binding. Project requirements for absolute hemolysis thresholds are documented in the narrative and referenced throughout the factor rationale text. The structured bindsRequirement field is not populated under the Minimal profile declaration, consistent with the reduced binding obligations of the Minimal conformance tier. Monte Carlo UQ results are accepted as sufficient uncertainty characterization for the current regulatory submission stage.",
